'''Gonzalo Aemilius''' (born 1978 in [[Montevideo]]) is a Uruguayan [[Roman Catholic]] cleric.

==Biography==
Aemilius grew up in a middle-class family and attended a Catholic school in Montevideo. When he came of age he discovered his vocation for a religious career.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elobservador.com.uy/noticia/229702/conozca-a-gonzalo-aemilus-un-cura-del-siglo-xxi/|title=Meet Gonzalo Aemilius, a 21st-century priest|date=13 August 2012|publisher=[[El Observador (Uruguay)|El Observador]]}} {{es icon}}</ref> After being ordained priest, he was appointed principal of the [[Liceo Jubilar Juan Pablo II]] in 2005; his contribution was vital for the development of this Roman Catholic institution devoted to poor children. At the end of 2012 he was removed from the position and sent to the parish of Puntas del Manga to start a new work.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://liceojubilar.edu.uy/noticias/2012/nuestro-director-el-padre-gonzalo-aemilius-pasa-la-posta |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20121228103410/http://liceojubilar.edu.uy/noticias/2012/nuestro-director-el-padre-gonzalo-aemilius-pasa-la-posta |dead-url=yes |archive-date=28 December 2012 |title=Our principal Aemilius |accessdate=2 June 2013 |publisher=Liceo Jubilar }} {{es icon}}</ref>

He has a yearlong relationship to [[Pope Francis]], who was an important supporter of the Liceo Jubilar years ago when he was Archbishop of neighboring Buenos Aires.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.elobservador.com.uy/noticia/246110/el-reencuentro-entre-aemilius-y-el-papa-jorge-soy-gonzalo-estoy-aca-/ |title=Aemilius reencounters Pope Francis|date=18 March 2013|publisher=[[El Observador (Uruguay)|El Observador]]}} {{es icon}}</ref>

