'''''Tafsir Urwa-Tul-Wusqa''''' is a ''[[tafsir]]'' (Islamic exegesis) claiming to disprove the [[virgin birth of Jesus]] by reference to [[Quran]]ic verses. This contradicts traditional Islamic views [[Jesus in Islam|of Jesus]] and [[Mary in Islam|of Mary]]. The text was written in [[Urdu]] by Abdul Kareem Asri, and [[Ahl-i Hadith]] scholar from [[Gujrat City]], Pakistan. It incorporates the ideology of [[Sir Syed Ahmad Khan]] with traditional Ahl-i Hadith thought.

